START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":65,\"repo\":\"bramstein/stateofwebtype\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Support tables for type and typographic features on the web.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-14T09:15:10.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.caniemail.com/\">Can I Email?</a> - Support tables for HTML and CSS in emails. Inspired by <a href=\"http://caniuse.com/\">Can I use</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-14T09:04:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/css-feature-toggles/aeinmfddnniiloadoappmdnffcbffnjg\">CSS Feature Toggles</a> - Chrome DevTools extension to toggle support of selected CSS features for testing progressive enhancement fallbacks.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-15T21:32:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jakearchibald.github.io/isserviceworkerready/\">Is service worker ready?</a> - Overview of support for all features involved in the core technology behind Progressive Web Apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-02-02T08:19:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ispwaready.toxicjohann.com/\">Is PWA ready?</a> - Overview of support for the core and related technologies behind Progressive Web Apps for both popular global and many Chinese browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-02-02T08:19:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/MDN/Contribute/Structures/Compatibility_tables\">MDN Compatibility tables</a> - MDN's web technology documentation has a browser compatibility table end the end of each article.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-28T10:26:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data\">MDN Browser Compat Data</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3360,\"repo\":\"mdn/browser-compat-data\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - npm module powering the MDN Compatibility tables.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-12-28T10:26:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.filamentgroup.com/dwpe/\">Designing with Progressive Enhancement</a> - <em>The book</em> (400+ pages) on Progressive Enhancement.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-03T21:47:25.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cognition.happycog.com/article/progressive-enhancement-its-about-the-content\">Progressive Enhancement: It's about the content</a> - Sharing content is the core of the web. Progressive Enhancement ensures access to content.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/enhancement/\">The Role of Enhancement in Web Design</a> - From the concept of enhancement to the criteria and rules for enriching the user interface.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://alistapart.com/article/understandingprogressiveenhancement\">Understanding Progressive Enhancement</a> - Apply technologies in an intelligent way, layer-upon-layer, to craft an amazing experience.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://adaptivewebdesign.info/2nd-edition/\">Adaptive Web Design</a> - Book on Progressive Enhancement from content to design and interaction.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://diveinto.html5doctor.com/detect.html\">Detecting (HTML5) features</a> - Intro to different feature detection techniques with examples and demos.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Concept</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://infrequently.org/2015/06/progressive-apps-escaping-tabs-without-losing-our-soul/\">Progressive Web Apps</a> - Enhancing web sites into native-like apps (progressive, not hybrid).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://articles.uie.com/progressive_enhancement/\">The Content-out Approach</a> - Provide wide access to content without technological restrictions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/technology/using-progressive-enhancement#make-the-page-usable-with-only-html\">Make the page usable with only HTML</a> - This sets the baseline for every device and browser.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://alistapart.com/article/testdriven\">Test Driven Progressive Enhancement</a> - Core functional experience enhanced after testing capabilities.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://responsivenews.co.uk/post/18948466399/cutting-the-mustard\">Cut the mustard</a> - Set a threshold for collection of enhancements.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sitepoint.com/an-introduction-to-css-supports-rule-feature-queries/\">CSS feature queries</a> (<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/API/CSS/supports\"><code>CSS.supports()</code></a> &#x26; <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@supports\"><code>@supports()</code></a>) - Natively test if specific CSS feature is supported using JS method or CSS declaration.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/feature-detect-es6\">Feature Detect ES6</a> - Detect which ES2015 features are available.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Attribute/requiredFeatures\">SVG requiredFeatures</a> - Render SVG elements only if their <code>[requiredFeatures]</code> evaluate to true.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://modernizr.com/\">Modernizr</a> - Extensive feature detection suite (supports custom builds).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://featurejs.com/\">Feature.js</a> - Lightweight feature detection suite.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://conditionerjs.com/\">Conditioner.js</a> - Conditionally load JS modules based on directives in HTML attributes.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Feature Detection</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.filamentgroup.com/lab/introducing-enhancejs-smarter-safer-apply-progressive-enhancement.html\">EnhanceJS</a> - Lets you asynchronously load CSS &#x26; JS after a set pre-defined feature tests.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://platform.html5.org/\">The Web Platform</a> - Overview of browser technologies with links to docs and test suites.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://caniuse.com/\">Can I use ...?</a> - Compare feature implementations and limitations across desktop &#x26; mobile browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.iwanttouse.com/\">I want to use ...</a> - Figure out the browser support of combinations of features.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://html5test.com/\">HTML5 Test</a> - Test and compare HTML5 feature support across browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://css3test.com/\">CSS3 Test</a> - Fine-grained tests for CSS3 feature support of your current browser.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://fontfamily.io/\">Font Family Reunion</a> - Compatibility tables for default local (system) fonts.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://html5accessibility.com/\">HTML5 Accessibility</a> - Compare feature support of HTML5 tags, input types and properties across major browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.powermapper.com/tests/screen-readers/aria/\">WAI-ARIA Screen reader compatibility</a> - ARIA roles and attributes support for different screen reader and browser combinations.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://whatwebcando.today/\">What web can do today</a> - Lists and checks modern web APIs like access to device system, sensors and actuators.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nolanlawson.github.io/html5workertest/\">HTML5 Worker test</a> - Compare which APIs are supported in Web Workers and Service Workers across browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://html5please.com/\">HTML5 Please</a> - Explore features with recommendations and links to polyfills.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/platform/catalog/\">API Catalog</a> - Lets you compare implementation of API specifications in major desktop browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://kangax.github.io/compat-table/\">Kangax's ECMAScript compatibility table</a> - Overview of JavaScript feature support across browsers and other runtimes.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://node.green/\">Node compatibility table</a> - Overview of JavaScript feature support across NodeJS versions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://iswebrtcreadyyet.com/\">Is WebRTC ready yet?</a> - Overview of support for the different browser features behind real time communication.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://iswebvrready.org/\">Is WebVR ready?</a> - Overview of support of different browser features behind WebVR including display, gamepad, audio and speech APIs.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Support Tables</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/scottjehl/Device-Bugs\">Device Bugs &#x26; Quirks</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/scottjehl/Device-Bugs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">853</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":853,\"repo\":\"scottjehl/Device-Bugs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Crowd sourced collection of weird HTML, CSS, and JS quirks in mobile devices, which you won't find in the other support tables.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://opendevicelab.com/\">Open Device Lab</a> - Lets you <em>test manually on actual devices</em> (for free).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Text-based_web_browser\">Text browsers</a> - Good way to test if your content is accessible at the baseline. Try <a href=\"http://lynx.browser.org/\">Lynx</a> for example.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dev.opera.com/articles/making-sites-work-opera-mini/#testing-in-opera-mini\">Testing in Opera Mini</a> - Download the app, emulate on desktop, setup to test local websites. (Opera Mini accounts for over 5% browser usage world wide)</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://curl.haxx.se/docs/manual.html\">cURL</a> - Web page to see the pre-rendered source code of a page.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.browserling.com/\">Browserling</a> - Lets you manually test web pages in different versions of browsers on Windows and Android platforms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/tools/vms/mac/\">Run Internet Explorer using Virtual Machines</a> - To test IE browsers on other platforms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SeleniumHQ/selenium/wiki/DesiredCapabilities\">Configure <em>Desired Capabilities</em> in Selenium</a> - Run automated browser tests in different scenarios.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/lighthouse\">Lighthouse</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/lighthouse\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">22.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":22382,\"repo\":\"GoogleChrome/lighthouse\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Audit and meassure performance of Progressive Web Apps (via cli or <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/lighthouse/blipmdconlkpinefehnmjammfjpmpbjk\">Chrome extension</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing Methods</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://adaptivewebdesign.info/1st-edition/read/chapter-6.html#the-progressive-enhancement-checklist\">Progressive Enhancement checklist (1st edition, HTML)</a>, <a href=\"http://adaptivewebdesign.info/2nd-edition/checklist.pdf\">Checklist of 2nd edition (PDF)</a> - Actionable list to check you've applied Progressive Enhancement best practices. Part of <a href=\"http://adaptivewebdesign.info/\">Adaptive Web Design book</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sitepoint.com/replacing-radio-buttons-without-replacing-radio-buttons/\">Fancy radio buttons</a> - Based on HTML radio buttons, visually enhanced using CSS pseudo classes and elements.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.filamentgroup.com/dwpe/checkbox-radiobutton/\">Checkboxes &#x26; radio buttons</a> - With custom focus, hover and checked state. Enhanced asynchronously.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ghinda.net/css-toggle-switch/\">Toggle switch</a> - Checkbox or radios, visually enhanced to sliding toggle switches using CSS only.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://lea.verou.me/2011/08/accessible-star-rating-widget-with-pure-css/\">5-star rating</a> - Based on HTML radio buttons, visually enhanced using CSS pseudo classes and elements.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/filamentgroup/jQuery-Slider\">jQuery slider</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/filamentgroup/jQuery-Slider\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">35</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":35,\"repo\":\"filamentgroup/jQuery-Slider\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Accessible, custom slider widget based on a standard HTML select.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.filamentgroup.com/lab/jquery-custom-file-input-book-designing-with-progressive-enhancement.html\">jQuery custom file input</a> - Article and library.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Custom Form Elements</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ghengeveld/react-isomorphic-form/\">React isomorphic form</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ghengeveld/react-isomorphic-form/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">30</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":30,\"repo\":\"ghengeveld/react-isomorphic-form\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Set of React form components which can be pre-rendered &#x26; handled server-side. They are enhanced client-side without losing state.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Data Visualisations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/progressive-enhancement-data-visualizations/\">Timeline</a> - From definition list to SVG illustration (article with demos).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Data Visualisations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.filamentgroup.com/lab/update-to-jquery-visualize-accessible-charts-with-html5-from-designing-with.html\">Charts</a> - From data table to themed charts using HTML5 canvas (article and library).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Images</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://filamentgroup.github.io/responsive-carousel/test/functional/fade-auto.html\">Responsive Carousel</a> - List of images enhanced into responsive carousel with various behaviour options.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-16T11:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Examples</h2><h3>Images</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/tvler/lazy-progressive-enhancement\">Lazy Progressive Enhancement</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/tvler/lazy-progressive-enhancement\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">189</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":189,\"repo\":\"tvler/lazy-progressive-enhancement\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> 